inn1.comm: Lee starts over the wicket and fires through to the keeper, the batsman shouldering arms first up
on a length, on the pads, turned to fine leg
oh! Good ball, some swing away, rising well from the length and Marshall is immediately forced to leave it
down the legs, and Lee just strays too far with the effort, Marshall is quick to jump into an extravagant leave
Lee corrects immediately, with a straight one which is just defended away without too much troble
tucked off the legs out to midwicket, Marshall off the mark now
fires through quite tightly across him, the batsman shoulders arms
some swing back in to the batsman, half-appeal, a bit of ball-watching going on but Gayle calls the quick single to the covers
some swing away, the batsman straightens behind it, it moves away, takes the edge but bounces well in front fo the slips
some siwng here, the seam nice and upright, desperate - but vain - calls of "Catch it" as the leading edge runs down to third man where Watson tidies up
outside off, some nice shape away and the batsman is quick on to the back foot, and to leave it, too. No run
again moving away from Gayle who lets it go through
left alone again, still that good shape and Gayle once more lets it go
fullish, on the off and middle stump line, shaping away a touch, squeezed of the outer edge to covers
gets across to a length delivery outside off and is hit on the pad. Lee asks the question. Hit outside off.
short of length, coming in towards middle and leg, dabbed to the on side
just outside off stump, full in length, covers the off stump and shoulders arms
a tad outside off stump, trying to tempt him into a loose drive but he resists and again lets it go past him
curving away from Gayle who lets it go through to the 'keeper
length delivery around the off stump, pushed to the off side
fuller, moves away at the last minute, Gayle is struck at the crease, opens the bat-face to adjust to the swing and runs it down to wide third man
shaping in towards middle and leg, beats the waft and it runs off the pad
again on the middle and leg line, coming in and Xavier plants his front pad across, tries to get his bat around it and the ball rolls of the pad to the  on side
moves this one across the batsman, left alone
lands on a length around the off stump and moves away, left alone by Gayle
on the off stump line, pushed to covers

beaten outside off. It cut across outside off stump, Gayle plants his front leg forward, then withdraws it, tries to push back and wastes valuable time in the process and in the end, tries to jab it but makes no contact
Gayle breaks free with a feisty cut shot. Short and not all that wide, he moved back and across and got into a nice position
just outside off stump, Gayle covers the off stump and lets it sail through to the 'keeper

lands on a length on the same spot as the last ball but instead of shaping away, it straightens and Gayle had already decided to let it go and it bounces over the off stump and brushes the pad en route to the keeper
lands it outside off stump, curves in a touch, Xavier gets across to push it cautiously to the off side

almost caught at covers by the diving Symonds. It was a full toss that swung in towards middle and leg, Xavier tried to swat it through midwicket and got the leading edge. Symonds dived full stretch but it fell short of him
on the off stump line, Gayle gets across to defend to the off side
on the off and middle line, Gayle leans forward to defend the delivery that straightened this time
kicks up from short of length, on the middle stump line, fended to the on side
leaves it alone outside off stump
swinging delivery full and well outside off stump, the swing started a tad too early in the trajectory and Xavier didn't have much problem in letting that one go through
hits the deck short of length, holds its line outside off stump, Xavier shoulders arms
full in length, around the off stump and Xavier gets across to defend . Xavier stands just outside the crease, taps his bat on the crease as he awaits the bowler

And very strange. Xavier doesn't even try to hit the free hit delivery. Compact defensive stroke. Lee is bemused and signals to Xavier the free hit signal and smiles. Gayle goes across to have a chat. I guess he didn't see the signal of the no-ball and free hit.
on the middle and leg, dabbed to leg side
not all that short, around the off stump line, Gayle moved his back leg outside off, opened his stance and in the end, stabbed it to the off side
again that exaggerated foot movement. The back leg goes back and across and lands just outside off stump, he opens his stance and then cuts a length delivery through cover point
he has decided to go for his shots. Again that back and across movement and he cuts a length delivery to covers
Meaty blow as Gayle goes down town. He walked down the track and scythed a full length delivery over long-off. He just stood there and admired the stroke. Now a long-off is in place
on the middle stump line and Gayle defends back along the track
drags back the length and moves it outside off stump, Gayle lets it fly past him
hurls it full outside off stump and Xavier goes hard at his off drive  and mistimes it towards mid-off
the surprise bouncer almost works. Xavier tried to press back but the ball got big on him quickly and he fended it and it popped up off the leading edge in front of him. Lee can't reach it
outside the off stump and left alone. Free hit next ball and Gayle walks across to let him know! Just making sure his young opener is aware.
X-Man breaks free. He moved outside leg stump and drills a full pitched delivery inside-out through wide mid-off.
full again and Xavier skips down the track and lofts it just over the  jumping Shane Watson at mid-on
leans forward to push it back down the track
hits the deck on a length and outside off stump, left alone
Blasted over midwicket. He moves right back to a full delivery, predetermined movement - he pressed back and opened his stance up - and whipped it over midwicket.
stays at his position and drives another full delivery hard to right of mid-on where a diving stop is made
on the leg and middle line, off a length, Xavier Marshall tries to turn it to square leg, misses and it runs off the pad to the on side
full pitched on the middle, driven to mid-on
X-man dances down the track. The ball is pushed across him. He brings his bat down and slices it over covers.
short of  length, coming into him and he takes out the bottom hand and tries to jab it to the leg side and it rolls off the pad
on the off and middle line, steered to backward point
slightly short of length and Gayle clears the front leg and pulls it through wide midwicket
again a touch short in length, another pull but this time he drags it towards deep square leg
short in length, outside off stump, guided through cover point

Simple technique from Gayle. The back leg goes back and across, the front leg is pressed outside leg and from that open stance he swings a short-of-length delivery to wide midwicket boundary. One bounce and over the ropes.
lands on the leg stump line and goes down leg, gathered by the 'keeper
crispy cover drive but Roy (Symonds) dives to his at right at covers to make a fine stop.
rotates the strike back to Gayle with a slash to Lee at third man
down the leg side and Ronchi makes a diving stop
just outside off stump, dabbed to backward point
full in length, on middle and leg, clipped to deep square leg
outside the off stump and left alone
beaten outside off stump, Delivered with a slightly round-arm action and slinged across in the zone outside off, Gayle pushed inside the line
just outside off stump, chopped to short third man region
slightly short in length and Gayle went for the pull towards wide midwicket but it flew towards wide long-on but cleared  the fielder
leans forward to push to the on side
on a length, around middle stump, slogged to deep square leg
gets forward to defend a length delivery to covers
leans forward to jab a length delivery to the off side for a single

dropped by Michael Clarke Xavier Marshall had charged down the track and had a heave but could only got a top edge, straight up. Johnson ran towards it, Clarke came rushing from point and Johnson let his team-mate to try catching that. But Clarke misjudged it completely couldn't even get a hand to it. Hmm ... It was the bowler's catch but he should have called it.
dabbed through to third man
fullish, on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
on the leg stump line, runs off the pad to short fine leg region
just outside off stump, chopped to left of backward point for a quick single. Marshall was ball watching but managed to scamper home.
on the leg and middle,  turned to short fine leg where Johnson fields
works a similar delivery past square leg
shout for lbw as Marshall pushes forward to defend. He was struck in front of middle and leg and the hawk eye suggests it would have hit the top of leg
leans forward to push a delivery on off and middle to covers
similar delivery and this time Xavier Marshall mistimes a drive over the bowler's head and will pick up couple of runs
leans forward to defend a length delivery around the off stump
turned to the on side for a quick single
outside the off stump, left alone
goes for the yorker, lands on the crease on the middle and leg line, dug out to the on side
lifting delivery on the off stump line, takes the bottom hand off the handle, taps it towards gully for a single
steered to wide third man for a single
stretches forward to jab it off bat and pad to the off side.
on the middle and leg, dabbed to the on side
pushes to covers
Gayle drills a full pitched delivery on the middle to right of long-on
Monster hit. He thrust his front foot out and swung a full delivery on leg and middle to wide long-on stands. 50 up for the captain.
full pitched outside off stump, driven to extra cover
turned to Lee at long leg for another single. The throw was flat, fast and on top of the stumps.
on the leg side, turned to fine leg for couple of runs

Gayle is run out. Oh what a way to go.Marshall had driven a fullish delivery back down the track and the lunging Johnson had got a hand on it and it went on to break the stumps and Gayle couldn't get back into the crease in time. He was in murderous mood but has to go back to the hutch.
leans forward to push a full delivery to the on side
gets behind the line of a length delivery on the middle and leg and works it to midwicket
starts off with a delivery well outside the off stump, the batsman tries to cut but can't connect
stays back to punch a length delivery around off to mid-off
swing and a miss. Short in length, outside off and Marshall tried to cut it hard but the bat went underneath the ball
gets back and across this time and chops it down to third man for a single
on a length, just outside off stump, Sarwan stabs it close on the off side and Watson rushes through to pick the ball up
outside the off stump line, left alone
just outside the off stump, Marshall is beside the line, tries to run it down to third man and is beaten
He cleared his front foot and flat-batted a short-of-length delivery over mid-off. Confident and aggressive
turned to the leg side for a single
bangs it short and it sails down leg
fuller but again down leg. Asad Rauf extends his arms
clipped to long leg for a single
leans forward to drive pleasingly to right of mid-off
full length delivery, pushed towards mid-off for a quick single
slower one on the middle and leg, turned to square leg

Super catch from Ronchi, diving to his right. He had gone down the track and tried to blast a wide delivery over the off-side field on a bent knee but got a thick edge. And Ronchi went flying to his right to pluck it. Viv Richards, on the wireless, says, "Marshall cannot be criticized for that shot. You can't be hars on him. The shot was on." He was trying to be aggressive. Great catch by Ronchi, though.
wide down the leg side  and it runs away to the boundary
on the stumps, pushed to mid-on
worked to left of midwicket for a single
gets behind the line of a length delivery and pushes it cautiously to the off side
fuller, on the middle and off line, pushed to the off side
stretches across to flick a delivery from outside off to midwicket
The falling sweep! Well not quite Kanhai but profitable. He stretched his foot out and slog swept a full delivery to deep backward square leg boundary and lost balance in doing so
played towards cover
another lofted sweep but this time it goes to deep midwicket region. He was trying to hit square but didn't middle it well.
gets forward to ping long-off
flighted full, driven back to the bowler
cutting in towards the off stump, steered to backward point
a tad slower , full in length, outside off, cut to left of backward point
slanted across Chanders who lets it go in his typical fashion: the bat goes inside the line and towards mid-on
leans forward to drive a full delivery well to the right of mid-off, Lee moves across and dives but lets it slip through his fingers
short of length, on the middle and leg, that length allows Sarwan to wrist it behind square leg
outside off stump, left alone
leans forward to drive a ball on the middle to long-off
outside off, steered towards short third man region for a single
full and down leg, swept to short fine leg.
slower through the air, Sarwan waits before cutting it late to short third man
flatter, a tad quicker, on the off, chopped to short third man again
fuller, mistimes a drive back to the bowler
length delivery outside off, defended to the off side
leans forward to drive to mid-off
outside off, angling away, he gets forward to tap it to Symonds at extra cover
slower one, full, driven to covers
around the off stump line, moving away and Chanders gets across to push it to cover point. Can't get that single he wants
full pitched just outside off stump, driven to long-off for a single
floated outside off, from over the sticks, driven to covers
on a length, just outside off, tapped to the leg side, they think about a single but change their mind as Ronchi rushes across
tries to paddle a delivery outside off and gloves it on to his helmet.
connects with the paddle shot this time and will get a single to fine leg
arm-ball on the off stump line, dabbed to backward point
stretches across to take a flighted delivery on the full and drives to right of sweeper cover where a diving stop is made
thrust his front foot out and creamed a full pitched delivery to the right of the umpire who jumps to his left
on the middle, wristed to deep backward square leg for couple of runs
Chanders tried to swing a length delivery from outside off over midwicket and misses. Sarwan walks over to have a chat.
on the off stump line, guided to point
outside off stump and square driven to deep backward point region where Hussey makes a sliding stop near the ropes to save two runs
pushed to extra cover for a single
short of length, outside off, cut to right of deep point region
steps down the track and taps a full length delivery to square leg
outside the off stump, Chanderpaul tries to paddle it but mistimes it close on the leg side and Ronchi goes across to pick up the ball
leans across to defend to covers
fuller, on the off stump line, driven to right of Clarke who lunges to make the stop
a tad quicker, fuller and Chanderpaul jabs it to the off side
floated outside off, driven to covers
lovely inside-out drive past the extra-cover fielder. He had driven the previous delivery uppishly and straight to the fielder but not this time
driven to deep cover for a single
floated on the off, driven to covers
slower in the air, on the middle, turned to midwicket
leans forward to retain the strike with a single to long-off
leans to work a full delivery to midwicket
stretches across to drive to left of sweeper cover
full and on the off stump line, whipped to deep midwicket
leans forward to drive a full delivery outside off to deep cover
just outside off, tapped to the on side of the track

goes back to cut to short third man. He needs to take singles more frequently, has ended up pushing straight to covers and midwicket on a few occasions. But he has corrected the equation with a few boundary hits.
flighted full, driven hard to covers
just outside off stump and Sarwan tries to play a late cut but misses
gets forward to on drive to long-on for a single
driven inside-out with the turn to covers
low full toss, driven to Hussey at deep cover
Shot boss! He drove a flighted delivery inside-out over extra cover. Eye-catching stroke
leans forward to push to the off side
short of length, cut to deep point
leans forward to whip  a full delivery to deep midwicket region
and this time down to long-off for a single
gets forward to tap it back to the bowler
on the off and middle, squeezed to covers
driven to long-on for another single
on the middle and leg, Chanderpaul waits for it to turn before nudging it behind square leg
another single to long-on.
drives past the diving Symonds to long-off
full in length, on the off stump line, Sarwan opened the bat face and guided it to left of short third man.
Ronchi snaps another good catch. Chanderpaul edged the intended cut shot and Ronchi managed to take it on the second attempt.
on the middle stump line, full, worked behind square leg
comes down the track and drives a full toss to long-on. He then practises hitting it towards midwicket
on the middle, worked to midwicket
down the leg side, turned to backward square leg
quicker, flatter, full, defended down the track
comes in towards off and middle, chopped to cover point
flighted full on the middle, driven to covers
steps down the track and drives past the diving Symonds to long-off
on the leg and middle line, swept to right of long leg
quicker, on the middle and leg line again, Sarwan goes back to work it behind square leg
on the off stump line, turning in, dabbed to the on side
goes back to whip a delivery turning into middle stump to deep square leg region and by the time Bracken got across from long leg he would pick up two
short of length, just outside off stump, steered to point
shuffles across to the off stump, tries to work the ball on the off to leg side but can only get it down the track
short in length, sitting up outside off, cut down to the ground and to point
beaten as Sarwan gets squared up. It was delivered like a off break and it spat from middle line to outside off with bounce

full and well outside off stump, Sarwan tried to blast it over extra cover but couldn't clear Symonds. Out for 31. Viv Richards says, "The intentions were pretty good but he just didn't get the height."
on the middle stump line, on a length, turned to the on side of the pitch
leans forward to push to cover point
turns in towards the off stump, defended down the track
goes back to work a delivery turning into middle behind square leg. The home boy gets a loud cheer from the crowd
comes down the track and drives inside-out to left of long-off
full toss, surprised Bravo pushes it back to the bowler
Given out lbw but he was struck outside off stump. Bravo went for a sweep, missed and it might have hit the off but he was struck outside the line. Richards says, "Very unlucky. Tough luck Bravo"
wide down the leg side
on the off and middle, jabbed to the off side
short of length, outside off stump, Fletcher, the home boy, moves back and across and cuts neatly to deep backward point boundary. Elegant. Well timed.
on the leg and middle, kicking up from short of length, turned to backward square leg
on the legs, misses the flick shot, runs off the pad
turned to square leg
goes back to turn a delivery turning in to midwicket
goes back to cut a short-of-length delivery to deep backward point
comes down the track and whips a flighted delivery to left of deep midwicket
turned to square leg
full and on the middle and leg, driven to long-on
goes back to punch a short-of-length delivery uppishly to right of midwicket
on a length, on the middle, pushed to mid-on. Ronchi is standing up to the stumps
leans forward to push a length delivery to right of mid-on for a single.
short in length, well outside off stump, cut to backward point
on the middle and off stump line, cut to backward point again
short of length, outside off and once more hit straight to backward point.
manages to get this dab cut past the backward point fielder and down to wide third man
leans forward to drive to mid-off
short and climbing outside off, he thinks about the pull shot but changes mind as the ball moves further outside off stump
again short and rising, Ramdin stays adjacent to the line and upper cuts it to third man
lovely off drive. He moved into the line of a full pitched delivery outside off and caressed it through wide mid-off.
full and further outside off, Fletcher crouches in an attempt to dab it to third man and is beaten

shuffles outside off, tries to pull a short delivery and it rolls to the on side of the pitch and they rush across for a quick single. Lee swooped on the ball and fired in a throw at the non-striker's end, misses and Fletcher dives into his crease. Had Lee hit, he would have been gone.
slower one full, whipped to left of midwicket where Ponting dives and almost scoops it up. Super effort from him to get there.
Ronchi is in the act again. Fletched walked down the track, tried to swing a length delivery outside off over midwicket, missed but Ronchi,standing up to the stumps, didn't.
down the leg side, clipped to fine leg
full delivery, driven towards long-off
slanted across, guided to backward point
bouncer from Lee, Ramdin sways away from the line
follows the bouncer with a slower one, full and outside off, squeezed to point
full pitched outside off stump, driven to Symonds at extra cover
short of length, outside off stump, cut down to backward point

Lee catches and throws the ball up in the air and doesn't realise it has been called a no ball. It was the high bouncer and Ramdin stretched his bat out high above his head, tried to upper cut it and only managed to edge it straight up and Lee rushed along to take the catch
rushes through the channel to Ronchi
short in length, outside off, cut to deep point
full pitched and driven inside out to left of long off and Symonds fires in a fast and flat throw to Ronchi who breaks the stumps but Ramdin had dived back into the crease in time.
short of length, mistimes the pull to midwicket
backs to the leg side and carves a full length delivery on middle and off to deep point
outside off, full, flashed to third man
short in length, around the off stump line, cut down to third man
smashes a slower one to deep midwicket boundary
banged in short outside off stump, cut to third man
Wicket no 300 for Lee. It was the slower one and Sammy was early into the intended lofted shot, edged it towards short mid-off region, Lee called for it early and pouches it safely.
pushed towards extra cover for a quick single and had Symonds found the stumps, Ramdin would have been out
the slow bouncer, Powell was too early into the pull and Lee smiles and Powell too has a laugh about it
driven to mid-on for a single
turns a length delivery to the leg side and they cross over for a single. Bracken hit the stumps at the non-striker's end but Powell was in
moves outside leg and cuts to backward point
he moved outside leg, tried to cut a short of length delivery but it was the slower one and he ended up chopping it on to his stumps.
full and straight, pushed to the off side
cut across the batsman who is beaten on the forward prod
banged in short, fended towards short cover for a single
short and climbing outside off, tries to upper cut it but can't wood on leather
picked up the slower one early, waited before lofting it straight down the ground
faster, on the middle and leg, Fidel was on the back foot expecting a bouncer, had a waft and will pick up a leg bye as the ball rolled to short fine leg

Lee the footballer does the trick. Powell had dabbed a short of length delivery close on the off side, set off for the run, was sent back and he slipped. Meanwhile, Lee had rushed along and kicked it on to the stumps. A neat little left footer.
outside the off stump, another slower one, swing and a miss
another swing across the line and the ball bounces over the stumps
bouncer catches Fidel by surprise and he fends it off in an ungainly manner to short leg
banged in short again, Benn takes his eyes of the ball but manages to connect with his swat-pull
Fidel moves outside leg and tries to swing a length delivery over midwicket but fails to connect
short-pitched delivery again, pushed towards short mid-off region for a quick single
another swing and a miss.
Bracken terminates the West Indies innings with a yorker. Benn charged out, had a heave but missed.

inn2.comm: good start. On target. Just outside off stump and Marsh is caught the crease, feet together and he searched for the ball outside off. beaten.
further outside off and Marsh lets this one go past him without any problem
again angling across Marsh but it lands outside off and so Marsh lets it fly past him
tries to bring this one back in but slips down leg side.
back to the outside -off stump channel, left alone by Marsh

Marsh is cleaned up by Fidel . It landed on a length around the off stump and curved in a touch, Marsh was looking to leave it, saw the straightening, tried to bring his bat down. Too late. Thin nick and it crashed into the off stump.
outside the off stump, left alone.
cuts in off short of length, on middle and leg, turned to square leg
leans forward to defend a length delivery on the off stump
homing in on the off stump, nudged down the track and Powell moves across to pick up the ball
cuts in from the good length, towards middle and leg, Watson tries to tuck it to the leg side but is struck on the thigh pad
fuller, on the off and middle, Watson flicks it to square leg, standing close
turns a full delivery from middle and off to long leg
lands on a length on the middle, straightens, Ponting opens up his stance to defend it to the on side
rushing through the channel outside off stump, Ponting lunges forward to let it go past him
fuller, closer to the off stump, driven to covers.
wide down the leg side
leans forward to push a full delivery outside off stump to wide third man
on a length, around middle, dabbed behind square leg
leans forward to defend a length delivery outside off stump
short of length, again that front leg moves towards off and he defends down the track.
fullish, on the off stump, mistimes a drive to the leg side
defends a length delivery close on the off side, Ponting thinks there is a single in it, Watson, wisely, doesn't share the thought
banged in short of length, outside off stump, Watto shapes to pull but mistimes it to mid-on.
overpitched outside off and Watson drives past the bowler and to the right of mid-off
cutting in towards middle, Watson tries to play around the front pad, misses and is struck high on the thigh pad
well outside the off stump, reaches out for it to cut to wide third man
outside the off stump, on a length, Watson bends his knee, tries to work it to third man but it runs off the face of the bat, along the ground, to right of second slip
short in length, outside off stump, pushed to cover point for a quick single. Sammy with the throw and had he hit Ponting would have been run out
drifts towards the pads, turned neatly to left of long leg
leans forward to drive with the full face of the bat to mid-off
gets forward and across and creams a full delivery through cover point
fires in a bouncer and Watson ducks
slower one outside off stump, full and defended to the off side
on a length, outside off stump, dabbed wide of slips
full pitched outside off stump and Ponting eases it through wide mid-off. Two superbly struck boundaries from Ponting. Is the wheel beginning to turn for him? he has been in awful form recently
cuts in of short of length, towards middle, clipped to square leg
And he pings the wide midwicket boundary now. He leaned forward to pick up a full delivery over the on-side field
short and on the off stump and Watson swivels of the front foot to pull it front of square leg
fuller and well outside off stump, slashed to right of third man for a single
swinging in to the leg and middle line and Ponting whips it through midwicket. He arrested the front foot movement, leaned across and wristed it away
The runs are coming in a hurry now. Watto powers a full drive through extra cover
full in length, straight on the middle, turned to square leg.
slower one, full, driven to mid-on
slower again, short of length, dabbed to third man
shout for lbw but was struck high. It came in from outside off, the bat came down outside the line and he was struck in front of middle and leg
leans forward to dab a length delivery to point
full and on the middle, trying to trap him but Ponting makes sure his front leg is not pressed across too much and defends
short in length, coming in, turned to midwicket
the slow bouncer - I had seen quite a few of them in the IPL - Ponting is made to wait, tries to swat it down leg but misses
leans forward to defend a flighted delivery on the off and middle line
he goes right back to cut a short-of-length delivery outside off through backward point
on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
leans forward to jab a full delivery bat and pad to the leg side
stretches across to push to covers
flighted full outside off, steered to point
length delivery outside off stump, Watson is beaten as he tries to chop it down to third man.
cuts in from short of length, towards middle, worked past square leg
coming in towards middle and, since Watson is on the middle and off stump guard, he can work it behind square leg. Anything on the middle or even middle and off, he turns it to the leg side
yorker on the middle stump line, jabbed down the track. That will be a good ball to bowl to Watson
short of length, just outside off and that length allows him to dab it right of midwicket
goes right back to defend to the on side
a tad short in length and Watson goes back to pull to wide long-on
leans forward to defend a delivery turning away from him and it runs off the outer edge past Bravo at short third man.
goes back to defend a delivery outside off
goes back to push at a spinning delivery and it runs off the outside edge
stretches forward to defend
full pitched outside off, driven to covers
shuffles towards off and tucks a slower one to square leg
change of pace again, full and well outside off, mistimes a drive back to the bowler
yet another slower one, dabbed to point region. No ball, though. Free hit coming up.
he moved to the off stump, as he did so often in the IPL games, and muscled a fullish delivery from outside off to midwicket boundary.
short one and pulled past square leg. He didn't middle that.
Too many slower ones in a row and Ponting picked this one up, waited before square driving it to cover point boundary
flighted full outside off stump, cut to short third man
this time he cuts through covers. And will pick up a boundary. He is hanging on the back foot, looking for every opportunity to cut
fuller, defended down the track
There you go. Again presses back and goes for the cut shot. Benn is pinging the short of length too often. Perhaps, he is wary of Watson charging out
Same delivery. Same result. And Watson raises his bat to acknowledge the cheers for his fifty.
on the leg and middle, full, tickled to square leg
just outside the off stump, cut late to third man
short in length, around the off stump, Ponting gets close to the line and pushes it cautiously to covers

Short in length and Ponting goes for his favourite pull  and it races along the turft to deep square leg and Powell was there to field but he let it slip through his fingers. Made a complete mess of that one.
on the off stump line, pushed to covers
full pitched and driven down the track
full and just outside off stump, Watson opens the bat- face and runs it to third man
short, too short and no pace, Ponting rocks back to drag a pull to deep  backward square leg boundary
leans forward to defend a length delivery to off side
sliding on to the pads, tickled to short fine leg
cuts in off a length towards middle stump, not at all short but Ponting goes back to cut it past point
short and wide, cut to point
on a length, outside off, defended to the off side
short of length, outside off, punched to sweeper cover
